					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803#post-4368664</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803/scp-1287#post-4368664</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 19 Sep 2019 14:56:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Doc Rot</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5653603</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Damn shame this thing ended up neutralised. Imagine how valuable it would have been to recover lost MTF agents with years of military and Foundation training and experience. Best of all my guess is a lot of agents consider their teams and even the Foundation as their family. Nice little scip and it was pleasant to see a benevolent reality bender for a change +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803#post-4219700</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803/scp-1287#post-4219700</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 15 Apr 2019 13:30:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Elogee FishTruck</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4037075</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Like what another user said on the first page of this discussion, this is &quot;strangely heartwarming&quot;. This whole time, I was thinking &quot;Who made this structure?&quot;, and I was pleasantly surprised when the maker was <em>in</em> the structure. While some things don't add up in my personal headcanon (I wouldn't see my Foundation terminate what are essentially researchers because they're created by an anomaly) but the final note is wholesome enough and it'll stick in my mind. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
