					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803#post-1792123</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803/scp-1287#post-1792123</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 08 Jun 2013 02:51:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>azzleflux</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1444699</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Dunno how I missed this a while ago. Anyways:<br /> - He did use it to keep himself alive. For a while, at least. You'll notice that he was in there for about seven years. The thing is (in my headcanon at least), reality benders can be powerful, but they still have limits to what they can do depending on certain types of benders. It worked for a while, still.<br /> - In my mind, as stated above, there are certain things that different types of benders can and can't do. One of which being the ability to actually bring someone back from the dead or not. This one could not, but still wanted to help.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803#post-1768283</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-648803/scp-1287#post-1768283</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 07 May 2013 02:20:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Major Blackwood</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1522871</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Wow &#8212; interesting and unique. A few things kind of confused me though:</p> <p>-How did the reality bender die of starvation/dehydration? Couldn't they just use their powers to keep themselves fed and hydrated?<br /> -Why would he need to even change visitors to the statue into missing persons? Couldn't he just use his abilities to find them or resurrect them?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
